ENTRY       EC 4.2.3.97                 Enzyme
NAME        (-)-delta-cadinene synthase
CLASS       Lyases;
            Carbon-oxygen lyases;
            Acting on phosphates
SYSNAME     (2E,6E)-farnesyl-diphosphate diphosphate-lyase (cyclizing, (-)-delta-cadinene-forming)
REACTION    (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate = (-)-delta-cadinene + diphosphate [RN:R09897]
ALL_REAC    R09897
SUBSTRATE   (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate [CPD:C00448]
PRODUCT     (-)-delta-cadinene [CPD:C20182];
            diphosphate [CPD:C00013]
COMMENT     The cyclization mechanism involves an intermediate nerolidyl diphosphate leading to a helminthogermacradienyl cation. Following a 1,3-hydride shift of the original 1-pro-S hydrogen of (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate, cyclization and deprotonation gives (-)-delta-cadinene.
